OL,3,CMemorial service for 55 victims of the
OL,4,CManchester Air Disaster, 40 years on
OL,6,FThe airport's head chaplain, Reverend
OL,7,FGeorge Lane, told the service: "For
OL,8,Fmany of us here today, the date August
OL,9,F22nd 1985 has been imprinted on our
OL,10,Fhearts and minds for every one of the
OL,11,Flast 40 years.
OL,13,F"For some of us, including those who
OL,14,Fweren't even born in 1985, the
OL,15,Fsignificance of this day has been
OL,16,Fsomething that we have only later come
OL,17,Fto appreciate."
OL,19,FThe disaster is often referred to as a
OL,20,F"defining moment in the history of
OL,21,Fcivil aviation safety."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
